# Basic System Information

## Lab Overview
This lab covers basic commands such as Ver and system info, used to gain information about an individual system

## Objectives
- Examine the different information available about a system
- Understand what the different categories mean
- Learn to navigate the command-line 

## Key Concepts

| ver | provides the Windows version and build number in a dot sperated numeric format |
| systeminfo | provides a general summary of the computerand OS running on it. Show information such as OS version, available physical memory and system model |
| set | shows the current stored settings that dictate how the command-line session and programs operate |
| Piping | takes the output of a command and uses it as input to another command |
| more | allows user to view large amounts of information page by page, making it easier to digest |
| cls | clears the command prompt screen |
| help | defines a command as to what it does and variables that can be used with the command |

## Security Relevance
Ver and Systeminfo allow a user to check to what extent the system has been patched and if that particular build is still supported by the vendor.
